com.vector.cfg.model.groovy.api

Interface IMdfReadApi

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    IModelReadApiEntryPoint

    @PublishedApi(value=ADDITIONS_ALLOWED)
 @PublishedApiDomain(value=AUTOMATION_IF)
public interface IMdfReadApi
    The IMdfReadApi API provides methods which allow retrieving MDF model objects in different ways.
    The mdfRead() methods provide entry points to start navigation through the MDF model. Client code can use the Closure overloads to navigate into the content of the found MDF objects. Inside the called closure the related MDF object is available as closure parameter.

    The following types of entry points are provided here:

    • mdfRead(TypedAsrPath) searches an object with the specified AUTOSAR path
    • mdfRead(TypedDefRef) searches all objects with the specified definition

      • mdfConfiguredRead

        @PublishedMethod
<T extends com.vector.cfg.model.mdf.commoncore.autosar.MIReferrable> IMdfReadSingleConfigurator<T> mdfConfiguredRead(TypedAsrPath<T> asrPath)
        Returns a configuration object for the object found with the specified AUTOSAR path. This configurator provides means to configure the read mode.

        This method does not limit the search to the ActiveEcuC!

        Remark: Even in post-build selectable models this method expects to find at most one object because script code will never run in an unfiltered context.

        Type Parameters:
        T - the (expected) model object type
        Parameters:
        asrPath - an AUTOSAR path
        Returns:
        the reader configurator

      • mdfRead

        @PublishedMethod
<T extends com.vector.cfg.model.mdf.commoncore.autosar.MIReferrable> T mdfRead(TypedAsrPath<T> asrPath)
        Returns the object found with the specified AUTOSAR path or null if not found.

        This method does not limit the search to the ActiveEcuC, so it can be used to retrieve any object with this path.

        Remark: Even in post-build selectable variant models this method expects to find at most one object because script code will never run in an unfiltered context.

        Type Parameters:
        T - the (expected) model object type
        Parameters:
        asrPath - an AUTOSAR path
        Returns:
        The found object
